UADataType.Description: Describes the possible job order commands.

Field.Name: Undefined
Field.Description: Undefined value, should never be seen.

Field.Name: Store
Field.Description: Command to store the job order in local storage, but not to start the order.

Field.Name: StoreAndStart
Field.Description: Command to store the job order and start it as soon as the Job Order receiver is ready to start.

Field.Name: Start
Field.Description: Command to start a stored job order as soon as the receiver is ready to start. Only the Job Orders ID is used to identify the stored job order, all other information is not used. No changes are made to the stored order. If multiple Job Orders have been commanded to Start, then the priority and timing values in the Job Orders shall be used to determine the order of execution of the orders.

Field.Name: Update
Field.Description: Command to update a stored Job Order that has not yet been started, with the new order information. All previously stored information is replaced.

Field.Name: Stop
Field.Description: Command to stop a started job order, report on any work done on the order, and remove the stored information. Only the Job Orders ID is used to identify the job order, all other information is not used.

Field.Name: Cancel
Field.Description: Cancel an un-started job order and remove the stored information. Only the Job Orders ID is used to identify the job order, all other information is not used.

Field.Name: Clear
Field.Description: Command to allow the Information Receiver to clear any maintained information on the Job Order (usually sent after a receipt of a Job Response with a status of Finished.) Only the Job Orders ID is used to identify the job order, all other information is not used.

Field.Name: Undefined
Field.Description: Undefined value, should never be seen.

Field.Name: Waiting
Field.Description: The necessary pre-conditions have not been met and the order is not ready to run.

Field.Name: Ready
Field.Description: The necessary pre-conditions have been met and the order is ready to run, awaiting a Start command.

Field.Name: Loaded
Field.Description: In situations where only one job may be in active memory and is able to be run, then the job is loaded in active memory, the necessary pre-conditions have been met, and the order is ready to run, awaiting a Start command.

Field.Name: Running
Field.Description: The order is executing.

Field.Name: Completed
Field.Description: The order has been completed and is no longer in execution.

Field.Name: Aborted
Field.Description: The order was aborted.

Field.Name: Held
Field.Description: The order has been temporarily stopped due to a constraint of some form.

Field.Name: Suspended
Field.Description: The order has been temporarily stopped due to a deliberate decision within the execution system.

Field.Name: Closed
Field.Description: The order has been completed and fully reconciled. No further changes, or restatement of actuals is expected.

Field.Name: Error
Field.Description: The Job is in error and requires attention.

UADataType.Description: It describes the possible return status from a Method call

Field.Name: Undefined
Field.Description: Undefined value, should never be seen

Field.Name: NoError
Field.Description: There were no errors in processing the method.

Field.Name: InvalidJobOrderID
Field.Description: The referenced job order ID is invalid or not known to the receiver.

Field.Name: UnableToAcceptJobOrder
Field.Description: The server is currently unable to accept job orders.

Field.Name: UnableToAcceptJobOrderCommand
Field.Description: The server is currently unable to accept job order commands for the specified job order.

Field.Name: UnableToReturnJobResponse
Field.Description: The server is unable to provide a Job Response for the specified Job Order.

UADataType.Description: Defines the information needed to schedule and execute a job.

Field.Name: ID
Field.Description: An identification of the Job Order.

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Addition information about the Job Order

Field.Name: WorkMasterID
Field.Description: Work Master associated with the job order. If multiple work masters are defined, then the execution system can select the work master based on the availability of resources.

Field.Name: StartTime
Field.Description: The proposed start time for the order, may be empty if not specified

Field.Name: EndTime
Field.Description: The proposed end time for the order, may be empty if not specified

Field.Name: Priority
Field.Description: The priority of the job order, may be empty of not specified. Higher numbers have higher priority. This type allows the Job Order clients to pick their own ranges, and the Job Order server only has to pick the highest number.

Field.Name: JobOrderParameters
Field.Description: Key value pair with values, not associated with a resource that is provided as part of the job order, may be empty if not specified.

Field.Name: PersonnelRequirements
Field.Description: A specification of any personnel requirements associated with the job order, may be empty if not specified

Field.Name: EquipmentRequirements

Field.Name: PhysicalAssetRequirements

Field.Name: MaterialRequirements
Field.Description: A specification of any material requirements associated with the job order, may be empty if not specified.
